{"schemaVersion":1,"bookId":"gre-random","unitId":"word-list-16","title":"Word List 16","sectionId":"gre-core","sectionTitle":"核心词汇","pageStart":194,"pageEnd":205,"extractionMethod":"ocr","wordEntryCount":125,"duplicateEntryCount":33,"pages":[{"number":194,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"WordList16"},{"type":"text","text":"词根/词缓预习表"},{"type":"text","text":"词根/词缓含义例词及释义"},{"type":"text","text":"词根/词缓含义"},{"type":"text","text":"例词及释义"},{"type":"entry","text":"neg","headword":"neg"},{"type":"text","text":"否认"},{"type":"text","text":"negate v取消；否认"},{"type":"text","text":"hilar"},{"type":"text","text":"高兴"},{"type":"text","text":"exhilarate v使高兴"},{"type":"entry","text":"vibr","headword":"vibr"},{"type":"text","text":"-ship"},{"type":"text","text":"表状态"},{"type":"text","text":"振动"},{"type":"text","text":"vibrant adj振动的：充满生机的"},{"type":"text","text":"hardship n. 困苦"},{"type":"entry","text":"brilli","headword":"brilli"},{"type":"text","text":"发光"},{"type":"text","text":"briliant adj 卓越的;辉煌的"},{"type":"text","text":"bell"},{"type":"text","text":"美好"},{"type":"text","text":"embellishv装饰，美化"},{"type":"entry","text":"alt","headword":"alt"},{"type":"text","text":"高的"},{"type":"text","text":"exaltedadj.柒高的.高贵的"},{"type":"text","text":"opt"},{"type":"text","text":"眼睛"},{"type":"text","text":"optical adj.视觉的；光学的"},{"type":"entry","text":"poign","headword":"poign"},{"type":"text","text":"刺"},{"type":"text","text":"poignant adj.令人痛苦的：尖锐的"},{"type":"text","text":"per-"},{"type":"text","text":"贯穿"},{"type":"text","text":"perspective n.观点，看法"},{"type":"entry","text":"negate","headword":"negate"},{"type":"definition","text":"v 取消(to nullily or invalidate); 否认(to deny)"},{"type":"note","text":"园词根记忆：neg（否认）+ate→否认"},{"type":"text","text":"[nr'gert]"},{"type":"entry","text":"antagonism","headword":"antagonism"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.对抗，敌对"},{"type":"text","text":"[en'taeganizam]"},{"type":"text","text":"animosity, animus, antipathy, opposition, rancor"},{"type":"entry","text":"obsequiousness","headword":"obsequiousness"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 追超(abject submissiveness)"},{"type":"text","text":"[ab'si:kwiasnas]"},{"type":"text","text":"servility, subservience"},{"type":"entry","text":"candid","headword":"candid"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 率直的(not hiding one's thoughts)"},{"type":"text","text":"['kandid]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：cand（白，发光）+id→白的→坦白的→率直的"},{"type":"text","text":"frank, openhearted, plain, straightforward, unconcealed"},{"type":"entry","text":"satiated","headword":"satiated"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj厌倦的，生腻的（tired of)：充分满足的(fully satisfied)"},{"type":"text","text":"['serfiertid]"},{"type":"note","text":"图联想记忆：sat（坐）+i+ate（吃）+d→我可以坐下吃东西了→充分满足的"},{"type":"entry","text":"ongoing","headword":"ongoing"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj进行中的(being actually in process)：前进的：不间断的"},{"type":"text","text":"[aingauin]"},{"type":"text","text":"ceaseless, continuous, endless, everlasting"},{"type":"entry","text":"subversive","headword":"subversive"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.颠覆性的，破坏性的(intended to overthrow or undermine an established"},{"type":"text","text":"[sab'v3:rs1v]"},{"type":"text","text":"government)"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：sub（下面）+vers（转）+ive→转到下面的→颠覆性的"}]},{"number":195,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"vibrant","headword":"vibrant"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.振动的；响亮的；明快的（bright)；充满生机的，精力充沛的（pulsating with"},{"type":"text","text":"['varbrant]"},{"type":"text","text":"life)"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：vibr（振动）+ant→振动的"},{"type":"text","text":"The attorney's vibrant voice and outstanding sense of timing were as useful to"},{"type":"example","text":"him as his prodigious preparation, attention to detail, and mastery of the law."},{"type":"entry","text":"host","headword":"host"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.东道主（one that receives or entertains guests socially)：（寄生动植物的）寄主，"},{"type":"text","text":"[haust]"},{"type":"text","text":"佰主(a living animal or plant on or in which a parasite lives)"},{"type":"entry","text":"settled","headword":"settled"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj固定的（fixed)"},{"type":"text","text":"['setld]"},{"type":"text","text":"settiedlife稳定的生活"},{"type":"entry","text":"pharmaceutical","headword":"pharmaceutical"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 制药的，卖药的(of the manufacture and sale of medicines)"},{"type":"text","text":"[,fa:rma'su:trkl]"},{"type":"text","text":"来自pharmacy（n.药房：药剂学）"},{"type":"entry","text":"deliberation","headword":"deliberation"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 细想，考虑(the act of deliberating)"},{"type":"text","text":"[dr,lrba'rerfn]"},{"type":"text","text":"cogitation, consideration, speculation"},{"type":"entry","text":"tempting","headword":"tempting"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.诱感人的(having an appeal)"},{"type":"text","text":"[temptin]"},{"type":"text","text":"alluring, attractive, enticing. inviting. seductive"},{"type":"entry","text":"compassion","headword":"compassion"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.同情，怜(sorrow for the sufferings or trouble of others)"},{"type":"text","text":"[kam'pae{n]"},{"type":"note","text":"园词根记忆：com（共同）+pass（感情）+ion→共同的感情→同情"},{"type":"text","text":"compassionate（adj有同情心的）"},{"type":"entry","text":"obsessed","headword":"obsessed"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.着谜的，沉迷的(considering sb. or sth.as so important that you are always"},{"type":"text","text":"[ab'sest]"},{"type":"text","text":"thinking about them)"},{"type":"text","text":"来自obsess（v迷住；困扰）"},{"type":"entry","text":"burdensome","headword":"burdensome"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.繁重的，劳累的（imposing or constituting a burden)"},{"type":"text","text":"['b3:rdnsam]"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自burden（n.负担，重担）"},{"type":"entry","text":"seriousness","headword":"seriousness"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.认真，严肃：严重性，严峻"},{"type":"text","text":"['siriasnas]"},{"type":"text","text":"留 The seriousness of the drought could only be understood by those who had"},{"type":"text","text":"seen the wilted crops in the fields."},{"type":"entry","text":"exalted","headword":"exalted"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 崇高的，高贵的(having a very high rank and being highly respected)"},{"type":"text","text":"[1g'z):ltd]"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：ex+alt（高的）+ed→崇高的"},{"type":"entry","text":"inherently","headword":"inherently"},{"type":"definition","text":"adv.固有地，天性地(intrinsically)"},{"type":"text","text":"[xn'hrrantli]"},{"type":"text","text":"Although scientists claim that the seemingly literal language of their reports"},{"type":"text","text":"is more precise than the figurative language of fiction, the language of science,"},{"type":"text","text":"like all language, is inherently allusive."},{"type":"entry","text":"prescient","headword":"prescient"},{"type":"text","text":"adlj. 有先见的，预知的(knowing or appearing to know about things before they"}]},{"number":196,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Word List 16 >>>"},{"type":"text","text":"Famed athlete Bobby Orr was given his first pair of skates by a prescienf"},{"type":"text","text":"Canadian woman who somehow *knew* he would use them to alttain sporting"},{"type":"text","text":"greatness."},{"type":"entry","text":"discourage","headword":"discourage"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.使气，使沮丧(to deprive of courage or confidence)：阻碍(to dissuade or"},{"type":"text","text":"[d1s'k3:r1d3]"},{"type":"text","text":"attempt to dissuade from doing sth.)"},{"type":"note","text":"园联想记忆：dis（除去，剥夺）+courage（勇气）→使气"},{"type":"text","text":"discouraging（adj. 令人气铵的）"},{"type":"entry","text":"politically","headword":"politically"},{"type":"definition","text":"adv政治上"},{"type":"text","text":"[pa'lrtrkli]"},{"type":"text","text":"国来自political（adj.政治的；政治性的）"},{"type":"entry","text":"opposed","headword":"opposed"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 反对的(set or placed in opposition)"},{"type":"text","text":"[a'pauzd]"},{"type":"text","text":"be opposed to 反对."},{"type":"entry","text":"warranted","headword":"warranted"},{"type":"text","text":"aol保证的；担保的"},{"type":"text","text":"['wo:rantrd]"},{"type":"text","text":"Despite many decades of research on the gasification of coal, the data"},{"type":"text","text":"accumulated are not directly applicable to environmental questions; thus a new"},{"type":"text","text":"program of research specifically adldressing such questions is warranted."},{"type":"entry","text":"particularity","headword":"particularity"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 独特性(the quality or state of being particular as distinguished from universal)"},{"type":"text","text":"[par,trkju'laerati]"},{"type":"entry","text":"resignation","headword":"resignation"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 听从,顺从(submissiveness);辞职(a formal notification of resigning)"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自resign（v放弃；辞职）"},{"type":"text","text":"[rezrg'nerfn]"},{"type":"entry","text":"quiescence","headword":"quiescence"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 静止上, 沉报(the quality or state of being quiescent)"},{"type":"text","text":"quietness, stillness, tranquility"},{"type":"text","text":"[kwi'esns]"},{"type":"entry","text":"idealism","headword":"idealism"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.理想主义(the act or practice of envisioning things in an ideal form)：唯心主义"},{"type":"text","text":"[ar'di:alizam]"},{"type":"text","text":"(a theory that only the perceptible is real)"},{"type":"text","text":"In sharp contrast to the intense idealism of the young republic, with its utopian"},{"type":"text","text":"faith in democracy and hopes for eternal human progress, recent developments"},{"type":"text","text":"suggest a mood of almost unrelieved cynicism."}]},{"number":197,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"appreciative","headword":"appreciative"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 费赏的;感激的(having or showing appreciation)"},{"type":"text","text":"[a'pri:fatrv]"},{"type":"text","text":"来自appreciate（v欣赏，感激）"},{"type":"entry","text":"unwarranted","headword":"unwarranted"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 没有根据的(unwelcome and done without good reason)"},{"type":"text","text":"[An'wa:rantid]"},{"type":"note","text":"图联想记忆：un（不）+warranted（有根据的）→没有根据的"},{"type":"entry","text":"poignant","headword":"poignant"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.令人痛苦的，伤心的（painfully affecting the feelings);尖锐的，尖刻的"},{"type":"text","text":"['poinjant]"},{"type":"text","text":"(cutting)"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：poign（刺）+ant→用针刺的→尖锐的"},{"type":"entry","text":"unsurpassed","headword":"unsurpassed"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj未被超越的(unrivalled)"},{"type":"text","text":"[Ansar'paest]"},{"type":"text","text":"unexceeded, unexcelled"},{"type":"entry","text":"persuasive","headword":"persuasive"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj 易使人信服的，有说服力的(tending or having the power to persuade)"},{"type":"text","text":"[par'swersIv]"},{"type":"entry","text":"exasperate","headword":"exasperate"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.激怒，使恼怒（to make angry:vex)"},{"type":"text","text":"[rg'zaesparert]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：ex（向外）+asper（粗糙）+ate→（说话）粗→激怒"},{"type":"text","text":"B huff iritate, peeve, pique, rile, roil"},{"type":"text","text":"exasperation（n.激怒，恼怒）"},{"type":"entry","text":"introspective","headword":"introspective"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj 内省的, 自省的(characteristic of sb. who is inclined to introspect)"},{"type":"text","text":"[intra'spektrv]"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自introspect（v.内省，反省）"},{"type":"text","text":"Unlike many recent interpretations of Beethoven’s piano sonatas, the"},{"type":"text","text":"recitalist's performance was a delightfully free and introspective one;"},{"type":"text","text":"nevertheless, it was also, seemingly paradoxically, quite controlled."},{"type":"entry","text":"ironic","headword":"ironic"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj挖苦的，讽刺的(sarcastic);出乎意料的（directly opposite to what might be"},{"type":"text","text":"[ar'ra:nrk]"},{"type":"text","text":"expected)"},{"type":"text","text":"It is ironic that a critic of such overwhelming vanity now suffers from a"},{"type":"text","text":"measure of the oblivion to which he was forever consigning others, in the end, all"},{"type":"text","text":"his self-adulation has only worked against him."},{"type":"text","text":"purchase"},{"type":"entry","text":"unlikely","headword":"unlikely"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.不太可能的(not likely)：没有希望的（unpromising)"},{"type":"text","text":"[An'larkli]"},{"type":"text","text":"improbable, unbelievable, unconvincing"},{"type":"entry","text":"transcendent","headword":"transcendent"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 超越的，卓越的，出众的(extremely great; supreme)"},{"type":"text","text":"[traen'sendant]"},{"type":"text","text":"ultimate, unsurpassable, utmost, uttermost"},{"type":"entry","text":"pomposity","headword":"pomposity"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.自大的行为或言论（pompous behavior,demeanor,or speech)"},{"type":"text","text":"[pa:m'pa:sati]"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自pomp（n.炫耀；盛况）"},{"type":"entry","text":"specialization","headword":"specialization"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.特殊化(making sth. become specialized)"},{"type":"text","text":"[spefala'zer{n]"},{"type":"text","text":"The new specialization of knowledge has created barriers between people:"},{"type":"text","text":"everyone believes that his or her subject cannot and possibly should not be"},{"type":"text","text":"understood by others."},{"type":"entry","text":"inspire","headword":"inspire"},{"type":"definition","text":"v鼓舞，激励(to impel; motivate)"},{"type":"text","text":"[in'sparar]"},{"type":"note","text":"园词根记忆：in（使）+spir（呼吸）+e→使…呼吸澎湃→鼓舞"},{"type":"text","text":"animate, elate, exalt, exhilarate"}]},{"number":198,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Word List 16 >>>"},{"type":"entry","text":"disinterest","headword":"disinterest"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.使失去兴趣(to cause to regard sth. with no interest or concern) n.无兴趣(lack"},{"type":"text","text":"[dis'intrast]"},{"type":"text","text":"of interest)"},{"type":"text","text":"disinterest in对无兴趣"},{"type":"entry","text":"exhilarate","headword":"exhilarate"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.使兴奋，使高兴（to make cheerftul)：使振作，鼓舞（to animate）"},{"type":"text","text":"[ig'zilarent]"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：ex（向外）+hilar（高兴的）+ate→使高兴"},{"type":"text","text":"圆exhilaration（n.高兴，兴奋）"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.（文学、艺术等的）类型，体裁（a kind of works of literature,art,etc.）)"},{"type":"entry","text":"tie","headword":"tie"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.平局，不分胜负（an equality in number)v.系，拴，绑（to fasten,altach, or"},{"type":"text","text":"[tar]"},{"type":"text","text":"close by means of a tie)"},{"type":"entry","text":"dietary","headword":"dietary"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 饮食的(of or relating to a diet or to the rules of a diet)"},{"type":"text","text":"['darateri]"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自diet（n.饮食）"},{"type":"entry","text":"ignoble","headword":"ignoble"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.卑鄱的(dishonorable, base, mean)"},{"type":"text","text":"[g'naubl]"},{"type":"note","text":"园词根记忆：ig（不）+noble（高贵）→不高贵的→卑都的"},{"type":"entry","text":"painstakingly","headword":"painstakingly"},{"type":"definition","text":"adv.细心地，专注地（fastidiously)：辛苦地"},{"type":"text","text":"['pernzterkinli]"},{"type":"text","text":"The President reached a decision only after lengthy deliberation, painstakingly"},{"type":"text","text":"weighing the divergent opinions expressed by cabinet members."},{"type":"text","text":"assiduously, exhaustively, meticulously"},{"type":"entry","text":"renown","headword":"renown"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.名望，声誉（fame）"},{"type":"text","text":"[r'naun]"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：re（反复）+nown（看作nomen，名字）→名字反复出现→名望"},{"type":"text","text":"For many years an unheralded researcher, Barbara McClintock gained"},{"type":"example","text":"international renown when she won the Nobel Prize in Physiology and Medicine."},{"type":"entry","text":"outweigh","headword":"outweigh"},{"type":"definition","text":"v比-重，比更重要(to exceed in weight, value, or"},{"type":"text","text":"[aut'wer]"},{"type":"text","text":"importance)"},{"type":"text","text":"outweigh"},{"type":"entry","text":"undesirable","headword":"undesirable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj不受欢迎的，讨厌的（not desirable,unwanted)"},{"type":"text","text":"[Andr'zararabl]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：un（不）+desirable（可取的）→不可取的→不受"},{"type":"text","text":"欢迎的"},{"type":"entry","text":"efficacy","headword":"efficacy"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.功效，有效性(the power to produce an effect)"},{"type":"text","text":"['efrkasi]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：ef（看作e，加强）+fic（做）+acy→做出了成绩→"},{"type":"text","text":"功效，有效性"},{"type":"text","text":"capability, effectiveness, efficiency"},{"type":"entry","text":"hardship","headword":"hardship"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.困苦，拮据(privation, sulffering)"},{"type":"text","text":"['ha:rd{rp]"},{"type":"note","text":"园联想记忆：hard（艰苦的）+ship（表状态）→困苦"},{"type":"text","text":"asperity, difficulty, hardness, rigor"},{"type":"entry","text":"informative","headword":"informative"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 提供信息的(imparting knowledge; instructive)：见间广博的"},{"type":"text","text":"[1n'fo:rmatrv]"}]},{"number":199,"blocks":[{"type":"text","text":"<<<GRE词汇精选乱序版"},{"type":"entry","text":"uninspired","headword":"uninspired"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.无灵感的，枯燥的(having no intellectual, emotional, or spiritual excitement;"},{"type":"text","text":"[Anin'sparard]"},{"type":"text","text":"dull)"},{"type":"text","text":"Although Simpson was ingenious at contriving to appear innovative and"},{"type":"text","text":"spontaneous, beneath the ruse he remained uninspired and rigid in his"},{"type":"text","text":"approach to problem-solving."},{"type":"entry","text":"address","headword":"address"},{"type":"definition","text":"v处理，对付，设法解决（to tackle sth.);致辞（to deliver a formal speech to)"},{"type":"text","text":"[a'dres]"},{"type":"entry","text":"insurmountable","headword":"insurmountable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.不能克服的，不能超越的(incapable of being surmounted)"},{"type":"text","text":"[Insar'mauntabl]"},{"type":"text","text":"impassable, insuperable"},{"type":"entry","text":"unmatched","headword":"unmatched"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj无可匹敌的（cannotbematched）"},{"type":"text","text":"[An'maetft]"},{"type":"text","text":"matchless, nonpareil, unmatchable, unrivaled"},{"type":"entry","text":"inexplicable","headword":"inexplicable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 无法解释的(incapable of being explained or accounted for)"},{"type":"text","text":"[Inik'splrkabl]"},{"type":"text","text":"国词根记忆：in（不）+explicable（可解释的）→无法解释的"},{"type":"text","text":"There were contradictions in her nature that made her seem an inexplicable"},{"type":"text","text":"enigma: she was severe and gentle; she was modest and disdainful; she longed"},{"type":"text","text":"for affection and was cold."},{"type":"entry","text":"embellish","headword":"embellish"},{"type":"definition","text":"v 装饰，美化(to make beautiful with ornamentation; decorate)"},{"type":"text","text":"[xm'belx]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：em（使）+bell（美好）+ish→使变得美好→装饰，美化"},{"type":"text","text":"embellishment（n.装饰：装饰品）"},{"type":"entry","text":"instructive","headword":"instructive"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 传授知识的(giving much useful information)，教育的：有益的(helpful)"},{"type":"text","text":"[In'strAktrv]"},{"type":"text","text":"来自instruct（v教导，教授）"},{"type":"text","text":"The parables in this novel are both entertaining and instructive."},{"type":"entry","text":"unencumbered","headword":"unencumbered"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 无阻碍的(free of encumbrance)"},{"type":"text","text":"[Anrn'kAmbard]"},{"type":"text","text":"lsozaki’'s love for detail is apparent everywhere in the new museum,"},{"type":"text","text":"but fortunately the details are subordinated to the building's larger formal"},{"type":"text","text":"composition, which is unencumbered by the busyness of much recent"},{"type":"text","text":"architecture."},{"type":"entry","text":"irritating","headword":"irritating"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj刺激的（irritative）：使人愤怒的，气人的（annoying）"},{"type":"text","text":"['rtertin]"},{"type":"text","text":"His critical reviews were enjoyed by many of his audience, but the subjects of"},{"type":"example","text":"his analysis dreaded his comments; he was vitriolic, devastating. irritating and"},{"type":"text","text":"never constructive."},{"type":"entry","text":"relieve","headword":"relieve"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 减轻,解除(to free from a burden; mitigate)"},{"type":"text","text":"[rr'li:v]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：re（表强调）+liev(看作lev，轻）+e→减轻，解除"},{"type":"text","text":"allay, alleviate, assuage, mollify"}]},{"number":200,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Word List 16 >>>"},{"type":"entry","text":"suspension","headword":"suspension"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 暂停(the state or period of being suspended); 悬浮"},{"type":"text","text":"今天暂停"},{"type":"text","text":"[sa'spenfn]"},{"type":"text","text":"To avoid annihilation by parasites, some caterpillars"},{"type":"text","text":"营业啦~"},{"type":"text","text":"are able to curtail periods of active growth by pre-"},{"type":"text","text":"maturely entering a dormant state, which is characterized"},{"type":"text","text":"by the suspension of feeding"},{"type":"text","text":"SALE"},{"type":"text","text":"abeyance, quiescence"},{"type":"text","text":"suspension"},{"type":"entry","text":"deprecatory","headword":"deprecatory"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.不赞成的，反对的（disapproving)"},{"type":"text","text":"['deprrkat>:ri]"},{"type":"text","text":"be deprecatory about 反对*"},{"type":"entry","text":"relevance","headword":"relevance"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 相关性(the quality of being connected with and important to sth. else)"},{"type":"text","text":"['relavans]"},{"type":"text","text":"来自relevant（adji.相关的）"},{"type":"text","text":"Adam Smith’s Wealth of Nations (1776) is still worth reading. more to"},{"type":"text","text":"appreciate the current relevance of Smith's valid contributions to economics"},{"type":"text","text":"than to see those contributions as the precursors of present-day economics."},{"type":"entry","text":"causal","headword":"causal"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj原因的，因果关系的（implying a cause and effect relationship)"},{"type":"text","text":"['ko:zl]"},{"type":"text","text":"图来自cause（n.原因）"},{"type":"entry","text":"descriptive","headword":"descriptive"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 描述的(serving to describe)"},{"type":"text","text":"[dr'skriptrv]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：de(加强）+script（写）+ive→描述的"},{"type":"entry","text":"exhaustiveness","headword":"exhaustiveness"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.全面，详尽，彻底"},{"type":"text","text":"[g'z:strvnas]"},{"type":"entry","text":"supportive","headword":"supportive"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 支持的(showing agreement and giving encouragement)"},{"type":"text","text":"[sa'po:rtrv]"},{"type":"text","text":"be supportive of 支持"},{"type":"entry","text":"competence","headword":"competence"},{"type":"text","text":"[ka:mprtans]"},{"type":"text","text":"来自compete（v竞争）"},{"type":"entry","text":"underestimate","headword":"underestimate"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 低估(to estimaite as being less than the actual size, quantity, or number) ; 看轻"}]},{"number":201,"blocks":[{"type":"text","text":"<<<GRE词汇精选乱序版"},{"type":"entry","text":"dispel","headword":"dispel"},{"type":"definition","text":"v驱散，消除(to scatter and drive away: disperse)"},{"type":"text","text":"[dr'spel]"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：dis（分开）+pel（推）→推开→驱散"},{"type":"entry","text":"succinctness","headword":"succinctness"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.简明，简洁"},{"type":"text","text":"[sak'srnktnas]"},{"type":"text","text":"conciseness, concision"},{"type":"entry","text":"indubitable","headword":"indubitable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 不容置疑的(unquestionable)"},{"type":"text","text":"[rn'du:brtabl]"},{"type":"note","text":"图联想记忆：in（不）+dubitable（怀疑的）→不容置疑的"},{"type":"entry","text":"feign","headword":"feign"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 假装,装作(to make a false show of; pretend)"},{"type":"text","text":"[fern]"},{"type":"text","text":"counterfeit, fake, sham, simulate"},{"type":"text","text":"feigned（adj.假装的；假的；不真诚的）"},{"type":"entry","text":"scenic","headword":"scenic"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 风景如画的(of or relating to natural scenery)"},{"type":"text","text":"['siinik]"},{"type":"text","text":"scenicift观光电梯"},{"type":"entry","text":"unproven","headword":"unproven"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.未经证实的(not proved or tested)"},{"type":"text","text":"[An'pru:vn]"},{"type":"entry","text":"commodity","headword":"commodity"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 商品(any article of commerce)"},{"type":"text","text":"[ka'ma:dati]"},{"type":"definition","text":"a drop in commodity prices 商品价格的下跌"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 怀疑的；多疑的(marked by or given to doubt)"},{"type":"entry","text":"skeptical","headword":"skeptical"},{"type":"text","text":"['skeptrkl]"},{"type":"text","text":"图be skeptical of 怀疑"},{"type":"entry","text":"unreasonable","headword":"unreasonable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.不讲道理的（not governed by or acting according to reason）;非理智的，过"},{"type":"text","text":"[An'ri:znabl]"},{"type":"text","text":"分BS(exceeding the bounds of reason or moderation)"},{"type":"text","text":"Although Tom was aware that it would be impolitic to display annoyance"},{"type":"text","text":"publicly at the sales conference, he could not hide his irritation with the client's"},{"type":"text","text":"unreasonable demands."},{"type":"entry","text":"obligated","headword":"obligated"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj有义务的，有责任的"},{"type":"text","text":"['a:bligertrd]"},{"type":"text","text":"beholden, indebted, obliged"},{"type":"entry","text":"homogeneity","headword":"homogeneity"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 同种，同质(quality of being homogeneous)"},{"type":"text","text":"[ha:madga'ni:ati]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：homo（同类的）+gene（基因）+ity（表性质）→具有同种基因→同种，"},{"type":"text","text":"同质"},{"type":"entry","text":"supernova","headword":"supernova"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.超新星"},{"type":"text","text":"[,su:par'nauva]"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：super(超级)+nova(新星）→超新星"}]},{"number":202,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Word List 16 >>"},{"type":"entry","text":"impermanent","headword":"impermanent"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.暂时的(temporary)"},{"type":"text","text":"[m’p3:rmanant]"},{"type":"note","text":"图联想记忆：im（不）+permanent(永久的）→不能永久的→暂时的"},{"type":"entry","text":"fret","headword":"fret"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.(使)烦躁，焦虑(to irritate; annoy) n. 烦躁，焦虑(an agitation of mind)"},{"type":"text","text":"[fret]"},{"type":"text","text":"cark, pother, ruffle, vex"},{"type":"entry","text":"impropriety","headword":"impropriety"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.不得体的言行举止(an improper or indecorous act or remark);不合适，不适当"},{"type":"text","text":"[,mpra'prarati]"},{"type":"text","text":"(the quality or state of being improper)"},{"type":"entry","text":"utility","headword":"utility"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 实用(fitness for some purpose or worth to some end); 有用(something useful"},{"type":"text","text":"[ju:'trlati]"},{"type":"text","text":"or designed for use)"},{"type":"text","text":"国词根记忆：util（使用）+ity→实用：有用"},{"type":"text","text":"We look with pride at our new bridges and dams, for they are works of art as"},{"type":"text","text":"well as of utity."},{"type":"entry","text":"scarcity","headword":"scarcity"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.不足，缺乏（a state of being scarce)"},{"type":"text","text":"['skersati]"},{"type":"text","text":"scarcityof.的短缺"},{"type":"entry","text":"explicitly","headword":"explicitly"},{"type":"definition","text":"adv.明白地：明确地"},{"type":"text","text":"[rk'splrsitli]"},{"type":"text","text":"definitely, distinctly, expressly"},{"type":"entry","text":"tragic","headword":"tragic"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 悲像的(of, marked by, or expressive of tragedy)"},{"type":"text","text":"['traed3rk]"},{"type":"text","text":"Though set in a mythical South American country, Isabel Allende's novel is"},{"type":"text","text":"rooted in the tragic history of Chile."},{"type":"entry","text":"evade","headword":"evade"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.躲避，逃避(to avoid or escape by deceit or cleverness; elude)：规避(to avoid"},{"type":"text","text":"[r've1d]"},{"type":"text","text":"facing up to)"},{"type":"note","text":"园词根记忆：e（向外）+vad（走）+e→走出去→逃避"},{"type":"text","text":"duck, eschew, shun"},{"type":"entry","text":"fused","headword":"fused"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj熔化的"},{"type":"text","text":"[fju:zd]"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自fuse（v熔化；融合）"},{"type":"entry","text":"inferable","headword":"inferable"},{"type":"definition","text":"ad能推理的，能推论的"},{"type":"text","text":"[xn’f3:rabl]"},{"type":"text","text":"图来自infer（v.推断）"},{"type":"entry","text":"unadorned","headword":"unadorned"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj未装饰的，朴素的"},{"type":"text","text":"[Ana'do:rnd]"},{"type":"text","text":"Rousseau's short discourse, a work that was generally consistent with the"},{"type":"text","text":"cautious, unadorned prose of the day, deviated from that prose style in its"},{"type":"text","text":"unrestrained discussion of the physical sciences."}]},{"number":203,"blocks":[{"type":"text","text":"<<<GRE词汇精选乱序版"},{"type":"entry","text":"serenity","headword":"serenity"},{"type":"text","text":"[sa'renati]"},{"type":"text","text":"As painted by Constable, the scene is not one of bucolic serenity; rather it"},{"type":"text","text":"shows a striking emotional and intellectual tension."},{"type":"text","text":"placidity, repose, tranquility"},{"type":"entry","text":"pop","headword":"pop"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.发出碎”的一声（to make or burst with a sharp sound）;突然出现（to go."},{"type":"text","text":"[pa:p]"},{"type":"text","text":"come, or appear suddenly)"},{"type":"entry","text":"opinionated","headword":"opinionated"},{"type":"text","text":"adlj固执己见的(holding obstinately to one’s own opinions)"},{"type":"text","text":"[a'pinjanertid]"},{"type":"text","text":"国来自opinion（n.观点）"},{"type":"entry","text":"thematic","headword":"thematic"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 主题的(of, relating to, or constituting a theme)"},{"type":"text","text":"[0i:'maetrk]"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自theme（n.主题）"},{"type":"entry","text":"unavoidable","headword":"unavoidable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 不可避免的(not avoidable)"},{"type":"text","text":"[Ana'vordabl]"},{"type":"text","text":"ineluctable, inescapable"},{"type":"entry","text":"singularity","headword":"singularity"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.独特(unusual or distinctive manner or behavior; peculiarity)：奇点(天文学上密"},{"type":"text","text":"[,singju'laerati]"},{"type":"text","text":"度无穷大、体积无穷小的点）"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自singular（adj.单数的；非凡的）"},{"type":"text","text":"The Gibsons were litte given to conformism in any form; not one of them was"},{"type":"text","text":"afraid of singularity, of being and seeming unlike their neighbors."},{"type":"entry","text":"proposition","headword":"proposition"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 看法，主张(statement that expresses a judgement or an opinion);提议"},{"type":"text","text":"[pra:pa'zifn]"},{"type":"text","text":"(proposal)"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自propose（v建议，提议）"},{"type":"entry","text":"coincidental","headword":"coincidental"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. I巧合的(resulting from a coincidence); 同时发生的(occurring or existing at"},{"type":"text","text":"[kau,rnsr'dentl]"},{"type":"text","text":"the same time)"},{"type":"text","text":"coincidentally (adv.巧合地)"},{"type":"entry","text":"venerable","headword":"venerable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.值得尊敬的，庄严的(deserving to be venerated)"},{"type":"text","text":"['venarabl]"},{"type":"text","text":"august, revered"},{"type":"entry","text":"ostentation","headword":"ostentation"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.弯示，炫耀（showy display:pretentiousness）"},{"type":"text","text":"[a:sten'tex{n]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：ostent（看作ostens，出现）+ation→拿出来显摆→夸示，炫耀"},{"type":"entry","text":"folly","headword":"folly"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.愚熹(lack of wisdom);愚囊的想法或做法(a foolish act or idea)"},{"type":"text","text":"[fa:li]"},{"type":"text","text":"foolery, idiocy, insanity"},{"type":"entry","text":"serviceable","headword":"serviceable"},{"type":"text","text":"adl.可用的，耐用的（fit for use）"},{"type":"text","text":"['ss:rvisabl]"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自service（n.服务）"},{"type":"entry","text":"spongy","headword":"spongy"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 像海绵的(resembling a sponge): 不坚实的(not firm or solid)"}]},{"number":204,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Word List 16 >>>"},{"type":"entry","text":"passionate","headword":"passionate"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.充满激情的(showing or filled with passion)"},{"type":"text","text":"['pae∫anat]"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自passion（n.激情）"},{"type":"text","text":"Though science is often imagined as a disinterested exploration of external"},{"type":"text","text":"reality, scientists are no different from anyone else: they are passionate human"},{"type":"text","text":"beings enmeshed in a web of personal and social circumstances."},{"type":"text","text":"ardent, fervid, impassioned"},{"type":"entry","text":"communal","headword":"communal"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.全体共用的，共享的(held in common)"},{"type":"text","text":"[ka'mju:nl]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：com（共同）+mun（公共）+al→公共的→全体共用的，共享的"},{"type":"entry","text":"radicalism","headword":"radicalism"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 激进主义(the quality or state of being radical)"},{"type":"text","text":"['raedrkalizam]"},{"type":"text","text":"来自radical(adj激进的：彻底的）"},{"type":"entry","text":"inventive","headword":"inventive"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj善于发明的，有创造力的（adept or prolific at producing inventions)：发明的"},{"type":"text","text":"[In'ventrv]"},{"type":"text","text":"(characterized by invention)"},{"type":"text","text":"The reader has the happy impression of watching an extraordinarily inventive"},{"type":"text","text":"and intellectually fecund novelist working at the height of her powers."},{"type":"entry","text":"flawed","headword":"flawed"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.有缺点的：错误的(spoiled by having mistakes, weaknesses, or by being"},{"type":"text","text":"[flo:d]"},{"type":"text","text":"damaged)"},{"type":"entry","text":"radically","headword":"radically"},{"type":"definition","text":"adv. 根本上(in origin or essence);以激进方式(in a radical or extreme manner)"},{"type":"text","text":"['raedrkli]"},{"type":"text","text":"When trees go dormant in winter, the procedure is anything but sleepy: it is an"},{"type":"text","text":"active metabolic process that changes the plant raolicallyc"},{"type":"entry","text":"expedient","headword":"expedient"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.权宜之计，临时手段（a temporary means to an end) adj(指行动）有用的（useful,"},{"type":"text","text":"[rk'spi:diant]"},{"type":"text","text":"helpful or advisable)"},{"type":"entry","text":"insulting","headword":"insulting"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj侮辱的，污蔻的（abusive)"},{"type":"text","text":"[rn'sAltrn]"},{"type":"text","text":"来自insuit（v侮辱，辱骂）"},{"type":"entry","text":"influential","headword":"influential"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 有影响力的(exerting or possessing influence)"},{"type":"text","text":"[,xnflu'enjl]"},{"type":"entry","text":"unintelligible","headword":"unintelligible"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 不可能理解的, 难懂的(being such that understanding or comprehension is"},{"type":"text","text":"[Anrn'telrdzabl]"},{"type":"text","text":"dlifficult or impossible; incomprehensible)"},{"type":"entry","text":"positive","headword":"positive"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 积极的(marked by optimism) ; 明确的(expressed clearly or peremptorily) ;"},{"type":"text","text":"['pa:zatIv]"},{"type":"text","text":"有信心的(confident)：无条件的(independent of changing circumstances;"},{"type":"text","text":"unconditioned) n. IE片(a photographic image in which the lights and darks"},{"type":"text","text":"appear as they do in nature);积极的要素或特点(an affirmative element or"},{"type":"text","text":"characteristic)"}]},{"number":205,"blocks":[{"type":"text","text":"<<<GRE词汇精选乱序版"},{"type":"text","text":"Although most worthwhile criticism concentrates on the positive, one should"},{"type":"text","text":"not indiscriminately praise everything."},{"type":"entry","text":"heavenly","headword":"heavenly"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 天空的， 天上的(of or relating to heaven or the heavens)"},{"type":"text","text":"['hevnli]"},{"type":"text","text":"celestial"}]}]}